title: Boys Soccer: Barcas, Crimson Knights exceeding expectations
text:
MORE It’s been a good past couple of weeks for Reilly Barcas and his fellow Wall boys soccer teammates.
Despite losing several key players from a team that reached the Shore Conference Tournament final last season, the Crimson Knights have remained undefeated on the season, only conceding one goal in a draw with Long Branch early in the season.
Last Tuesday, Reilly Barcas had an early goal-of-the-year candidate against Red Bank Catholic, hitting a midair volley off a short clear from the Casey goalie.
It was captured by fellow Wall student Ben Kelder and tweeted out for the world to see. Although it didn’t make "SportsCenter" Top 10 plays, the tweet received close to 100 retweets and 167 favorites in just a few days.
